1
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:13,278
It's good to be home.

2
00:03:18,152 --> 00:03:20,285
She's probably not there.

3
00:03:21,024 --> 00:03:22,504
She's there.

4
00:03:22,548 --> 00:03:24,289
Don't you want to go home first?

5
00:03:25,290 --> 00:03:26,552
After.

6
00:03:28,597 --> 00:03:30,425
Suppose she's found
someone else.

7
00:03:30,469 --> 00:03:31,731
She hasn't.

8
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:35,996
Okay.
Hope you're right.

9
00:03:36,039 --> 00:03:37,302
I am right.

10
00:03:58,540 --> 00:04:00,194
Ferruccio.

11
00:04:16,036 --> 00:04:18,038
This one is good.
Yeah.

12
00:04:25,393 --> 00:04:26,568
Ferruccio!

13
00:04:26,612 --> 00:04:28,614
- Ferruccio! Ferruccio!
- Ferruccio!

14
00:04:28,657 --> 00:04:31,530
- Yes!
- Ferruccio! Ferruccio!

15
00:04:31,573 --> 00:04:35,664
Stop hugging me!
I'm home. I'm not dead!

16
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:38,580
But you're in one piece
and we prayed for that.

17
00:04:59,035 --> 00:05:00,385
Ferruccio.

18
00:05:13,093 --> 00:05:14,224
Careful.

19
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:18,141
It's good. Isn't it?

20
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:20,579
- Fantastic.
- Oh!

21
00:05:22,232 --> 00:05:24,017
Don't touch it.

22
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:25,366
Okay, miss.

23
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:27,977
- Okay.

24
00:05:35,028 --> 00:05:36,421
The world has changed.

25
00:05:36,464 --> 00:05:38,858
Farming isn't
everything anymore.

26
00:05:38,901 --> 00:05:41,077
Not in Cento.
Not even Italy.

27
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:44,472
We find a place in the city.

28
00:05:44,516 --> 00:05:46,474
A little apartment.
And a garage.

29
00:05:46,518 --> 00:05:48,215
What about the farm?

30
00:05:48,258 --> 00:05:50,304
I don't want it, Papa.

31
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:56,005
Give it to them.
They've worked for it.

32
00:05:57,877 --> 00:05:59,705
I have an idea
to start a company.

33
00:05:59,748 --> 00:06:01,446
To build tractors.

34
00:06:02,447 --> 00:06:04,536
Smaller, cheaper tractors

35
00:06:04,579 --> 00:06:07,016
than the ones
that are being made now.

36
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,627
You're a farmer.

37
00:06:10,063 --> 00:06:12,805
You think I was a farmer
in the war, Papa?

38
00:06:12,848 --> 00:06:15,372
I was a mechanic.

39
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,940
I learned about machines,
about cars and engines.

40
00:06:17,984 --> 00:06:19,551
Did I raise a fool?

41
00:06:19,594 --> 00:06:22,641
The only company
that sells tractors in Cento

42
00:06:22,684 --> 00:06:25,861
is Cugini Randi.
Everyone knows that.

43
00:06:25,905 --> 00:06:27,210
But they don't have
the best tractors.

44
00:06:27,254 --> 00:06:28,734
They have the only tractors.

45
00:06:28,777 --> 00:06:30,431
If I make a better tractor,
for less money,

46
00:06:30,475 --> 00:06:31,693
people will buy mine.

47
00:06:33,608 --> 00:06:35,480
We have a plan, Papa.

48
00:06:35,523 --> 00:06:38,134
We're going to race
in the Terra dei Motori.

49
00:06:38,178 --> 00:06:41,529
And if we win, when we win,

50
00:06:41,573 --> 00:06:42,791
we'll use the prestige

51
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:44,880
to raise the money
for the first tractor.

52
00:06:44,924 --> 00:06:47,840
- Who is we?
- Matteo and me.

53
00:06:47,883 --> 00:06:50,930
- Who's Matteo?
- My friend.

54
00:06:50,973 --> 00:06:53,628
- You have a race car?
- We're going to make one.

55
00:06:53,672 --> 00:06:54,760
You can make a car?

56
00:06:54,803 --> 00:06:57,763
We're buying
an old Topolino for nothing.

57
00:06:57,806 --> 00:07:00,809
We're redesigning the engine,
increasing the displacement.

58
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:04,030
Turning the 500cc into a 650cc.

59
00:07:04,073 --> 00:07:08,556
I have also an idea
for a new cylinder head,
with overhead valves.

60
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,732
I can make it with bronze.
Cheap, easy.

61
00:07:12,038 --> 00:07:13,822
It'll be as fast or faster

62
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:15,171
than any car in the race, Papa.

63
00:07:17,565 --> 00:07:19,828
I can do this.

64
00:07:19,872 --> 00:07:22,265
I can make the lives
of every farmer like you better.

65
00:07:24,616 --> 00:07:28,533
With a tractor, you can compete
with the big companies.

66
00:07:30,926 --> 00:07:33,276
How do you know
your tractor will work?

67
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,277
We'll make it work.

68
00:07:34,321 --> 00:07:35,931
How do you know it'll be cheap?

69
00:07:35,975 --> 00:07:38,151
We'll make it cheap.

70
00:07:38,194 --> 00:07:41,023
Papa, even the government
knows the world has changed.

71
00:07:41,067 --> 00:07:44,244
It's helping new companies
with loans to rebuild Italy.

72
00:07:48,074 --> 00:07:50,642
And if nobody
buys your tractors?

73
00:07:50,685 --> 00:07:54,167
"A man who's not in debt
has no reason to work."

74
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:56,735
How many times
have you told me that?

75
00:08:00,434 --> 00:08:02,567
It's not impossible
what I'm talking about.

76
00:08:02,610 --> 00:08:06,832
The sun rises
and the sun sets for most men,
and they die.

77
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:11,488
But for some, for great men,
their name lives on.

78
00:08:18,670 --> 00:08:20,367
I want the Lamborghini name
to live on.

79
00:08:21,673 --> 00:08:23,979
I want the world
to never forget my name.

80
00:08:25,415 --> 00:08:26,591
Our name.

81
00:08:32,509 --> 00:08:33,728
Our name?

82
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:44,521
This one is not good,
Ferruccio.

83
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:54,619
You'll throw your life away.

84
00:08:56,751 --> 00:09:00,102
But what better way to do it
than in search of greatness.

85
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,367
Why can't you believe in me?

86
00:09:07,719 --> 00:09:09,721
I believe in what I can see.

87
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,545
Everybody!

88
00:10:43,118 --> 00:10:46,948
Nine, eight, seven, six...

89
00:10:46,992 --> 00:10:52,519
- Ferruccio!
- ...five, four, three,
two, one.

90
00:10:52,562 --> 00:10:55,217
- Happy New Year!
- Happy New Year.

91
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,354
I want to love you forever...

92
00:11:02,485 --> 00:11:04,923
until time stands still.

93
00:11:06,011 --> 00:11:08,056
Can I do that?

94
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,711
Only forever. No longer.

95
00:11:49,706 --> 00:11:51,143
Ladies and gentlemen,

96
00:11:51,186 --> 00:11:54,189
welcome to
the Terra dei Motori.

97
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:56,017
The great Enzo Ferrari

98
00:11:56,061 --> 00:11:58,541
will be delivering
the first-place prize

99
00:11:58,585 --> 00:12:01,066
to the winner
of the Terra dei Motori

100
00:12:02,937 --> 00:12:06,593
Mr. Ferrari has parted ways
with Alfa Romeo

101
00:12:06,636 --> 00:12:10,249
and will bring his own car

102
00:12:10,292 --> 00:12:12,599
The Ferrari 166 S.

103
00:12:14,340 --> 00:12:18,083
Thank you. I'm so proud
of this beautiful car,

104
00:12:18,126 --> 00:12:20,433
- it's like a dream come true.
- What are you doing?

105
00:12:20,476 --> 00:12:24,306
Ferrari. He stands
like he owns the world.

106
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:28,528
To see my cavallino
with my name on my own car,
it's beautiful.

107
00:12:28,571 --> 00:12:30,704
- He does.
- Thank you.

108
00:12:38,581 --> 00:12:40,627
And the race is about to begin.

109
00:12:40,670 --> 00:12:42,455
Ferruccio, come on!

110
00:12:50,898 --> 00:12:53,161
Signor Ferrari
will drop the flag.

111
00:12:53,205 --> 00:12:55,076
- One...
- Okay.

112
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:57,687
...two... three!

113
00:13:17,272 --> 00:13:18,404
We need more speed!

114
00:13:27,195 --> 00:13:28,805
Go! Go! Go!

115
00:13:46,562 --> 00:13:48,782
Go... go. Go!

116
00:14:00,968 --> 00:14:03,275
After the church,
there are two lanes.

117
00:14:03,318 --> 00:14:04,972
We can overtake them there.

118
00:14:08,149 --> 00:14:09,803
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

119
00:14:12,066 --> 00:14:15,678
Number two is trying to pass!

120
00:14:15,722 --> 00:14:18,943
- Don't let them pass!
- Just shut up, Ferruccio!

121
00:14:20,596 --> 00:14:22,685
Don't let them pass!

122
00:14:22,729 --> 00:14:24,296
Get ahead of him!
Get ahead of him!

123
00:14:34,219 --> 00:14:36,264
Get ahead of him!
Get ahead of him!

124
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:38,092
It's not wide enough!

125
00:14:38,136 --> 00:14:39,659
Go! Go! Go! Go!

126
00:14:39,702 --> 00:14:42,227
- Take the lane, Matteo!
- There's no room!

127
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:44,751
Take the lane before the turn!

128
00:14:44,794 --> 00:14:47,275
- We don't have the speed!
- We can beat them!

129
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:49,321
- We will never make it!
- For God's sake!

130
00:14:49,364 --> 00:14:51,105
- What are you doing?

131
00:14:51,149 --> 00:14:53,499
- Are you crazy?

132
00:15:55,909 --> 00:15:57,432
Breakfast.

133
00:16:01,219 --> 00:16:02,350
Breakfast.

134
00:16:02,394 --> 00:16:04,787
- I don't want anything.
- Yes, you do.

135
00:16:04,831 --> 00:16:06,311
Ferruccio, breakfast.

136
00:16:10,054 --> 00:16:10,967
We could've won.

137
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:14,275
We could've won!

138
00:16:14,319 --> 00:16:16,408
- We could've died.
- You should have died!

139
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:32,467
What is it, huh?
What's wrong?

140
00:16:32,511 --> 00:16:34,817
We lost the race.

141
00:16:34,861 --> 00:16:37,342
Everything we worked for,
it's over.

142
00:16:37,385 --> 00:16:38,952
It's not that.

143
00:16:40,301 --> 00:16:41,520
What are you afraid of?

144
00:16:41,563 --> 00:16:43,261
What?

145
00:16:43,304 --> 00:16:45,001
There's something
wrong with your ears?

146
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:48,875
Yesterday they were fine.
What are you afraid of?

147
00:16:48,918 --> 00:16:52,008
Nothing. All my fears
already came true.

148
00:16:52,835 --> 00:16:54,141
Say it.

149
00:16:55,447 --> 00:16:56,752
Say it.

150
00:17:00,495 --> 00:17:02,236
I'm afraid
that I'm not good enough.

151
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:07,241
That I-I did not win the race
not because of Matteo,

152
00:17:07,285 --> 00:17:11,289
but because I did
something wrong,
and I don't know what it was.

153
00:17:12,377 --> 00:17:14,118
That's what scares me the most.

154
00:17:17,338 --> 00:17:19,340
And I don't know
what to do next.

155
00:17:20,341 --> 00:17:22,474
What if I'm a fake?

156
00:17:22,517 --> 00:17:24,867
What if I'm not
who I think I am?

157
00:17:24,911 --> 00:17:27,348
What happens then?

158
00:17:27,392 --> 00:17:28,958
You're not a fake.

159
00:17:29,785 --> 00:17:31,178
I believe in you.

160
00:17:31,222 --> 00:17:34,094
I believe in every dream
you've ever had.

161
00:17:34,138 --> 00:17:37,576
And every one of them
will come true.

162
00:17:37,619 --> 00:17:39,534
You just haven't found
a way yet.

163
00:17:39,578 --> 00:17:41,841
Eat.

164
00:17:47,586 --> 00:17:51,372
What about
your rowing machine idea?
That was a good one.

165
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:55,463
Nobody needs to lose weight.
All the women got skinny
during the war.

166
00:17:55,507 --> 00:17:59,032
I might need one in...

167
00:17:59,075 --> 00:18:03,210
I don't know,
eight, nine months.

168
00:18:06,648 --> 00:18:09,956
I said I might need
a weight loss machine
in about nine months.

169
00:18:09,999 --> 00:18:11,958
I heard you. I was thinking.

170
00:18:12,001 --> 00:18:14,787
She's having a baby,
you fool!

171
00:18:20,836 --> 00:18:23,448
- Really?
- No, I'm joking.

172
00:18:23,491 --> 00:18:25,754
Because it's such a good time
to do that.

173
00:18:28,279 --> 00:18:29,932
It's going to be alright.

174
00:18:31,673 --> 00:18:33,284
You'll be a great father.

175
00:18:37,766 --> 00:18:40,247
I think we should
call him Matteo.

176
00:19:31,298 --> 00:19:32,560
Ciao, Papa.

177
00:19:54,582 --> 00:19:55,801
You're okay?

178
00:19:56,715 --> 00:19:58,064
I'm okay.

179
00:19:58,107 --> 00:19:59,500
Huh.

180
00:19:59,544 --> 00:20:00,936
Clelia?

181
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:02,460
Yes, everything's fine.

182
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:08,379
You want me to help?

183
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:10,642
You need money?

184
00:20:11,686 --> 00:20:12,731
Yes.

185
00:20:16,212 --> 00:20:17,692
I'll pay it back.

186
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:29,313
I don't have much.

187
00:20:31,402 --> 00:20:33,186
But I'll give you what I have.

188
00:20:38,844 --> 00:20:40,324
It's not enough, Papa.

189
00:20:41,716 --> 00:20:43,588
I have an idea.
It will be hard.

190
00:20:44,632 --> 00:20:46,504
But it will work.

191
00:20:46,547 --> 00:20:49,202
This time I know it will work.

192
00:20:49,245 --> 00:20:51,378
I promise.

193
00:20:51,422 --> 00:20:54,512
If you do this,
I'll pay it back with interest.

194
00:20:56,035 --> 00:20:57,210
Interest?

195
00:20:58,472 --> 00:20:59,517
Yes.

196
00:22:07,889 --> 00:22:09,413
He mortgaged the farm?

197
00:22:12,459 --> 00:22:14,243
You asked him to do this?

198
00:22:14,287 --> 00:22:15,854
He's my father.

199
00:22:15,897 --> 00:22:19,640
He's a husband to your mother
and a father to your brothers.

200
00:22:19,684 --> 00:22:21,207
I'll pay it back.

201
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:22,861
That's not the point.

202
00:22:22,904 --> 00:22:25,037
It is not his to give you.

203
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:28,170
It is your brothers'.
It is their farm.

204
00:22:28,214 --> 00:22:31,043
They worked for it.
Their whole lives
they worked for it.

205
00:22:31,086 --> 00:22:34,655
You said it yourself.
They deserve it.

206
00:22:34,699 --> 00:22:36,222
You don't believe in me?

207
00:22:36,265 --> 00:22:38,833
I believe in you, Ferruccio.

208
00:22:38,877 --> 00:22:41,401
I believe in you more than
you believe in yourself.

209
00:22:42,489 --> 00:22:44,143
But we will find another way.

210
00:22:45,797 --> 00:22:48,277
This is selfish.

211
00:22:48,321 --> 00:22:51,237
You will not put the future
of your family in danger.

212
00:22:53,282 --> 00:22:55,937
They have their own dreams.

213
00:22:55,981 --> 00:22:58,070
I would never let them
lose their farm.

214
00:22:58,113 --> 00:22:59,767
Things go wrong.

215
00:22:59,811 --> 00:23:02,944
No matter your intentions,
things go wrong.

216
00:23:03,902 --> 00:23:06,600
Don't do this, Ferruccio!

217
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:10,778
No good will come of it,
I can feel it.

218
00:23:12,650 --> 00:23:16,175
He only gave it to you
because you asked him.

219
00:23:16,218 --> 00:23:17,742
He gave it to me
because he believes in me.

220
00:23:17,785 --> 00:23:20,484
No. Because he pities you.

221
00:23:24,836 --> 00:23:26,402
Give it back.

222
00:23:30,102 --> 00:23:33,584
He won't take it back.
I know him.

223
00:23:33,627 --> 00:23:38,719
Then you go to
the bank yourself,
and deposit it in his account.

224
00:24:20,195 --> 00:24:21,762
I'll take the next customer.

225
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:30,205
Ferruccio! It's Vito.
Vito Rossi!

226
00:24:30,249 --> 00:24:31,598
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah.

227
00:24:31,642 --> 00:24:32,991
- How've you been?
- Good.

228
00:24:33,034 --> 00:24:35,210
How's your father?
Your brothers?

229
00:24:35,254 --> 00:24:36,560
Very good.
Everybody's good.

230
00:24:36,603 --> 00:24:38,518
Excellent. Have a seat.

231
00:24:40,346 --> 00:24:41,695
So, what can I do for you?

232
00:24:41,739 --> 00:24:43,436
I'd like to open an account.

233
00:24:43,479 --> 00:24:44,698
Of course.

234
00:24:46,787 --> 00:24:48,572
In your name, I assume.

235
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:53,968
Ferruccio in what name
would you like the account.

236
00:24:55,666 --> 00:24:58,756
My name... Ferruccio.

237
00:24:59,757 --> 00:25:02,498
Ferruccio Lamborghini.

238
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:04,283
- Great.

239
00:25:04,326 --> 00:25:05,937
Can I smoke a cigarette?

240
00:25:05,980 --> 00:25:07,199
Of course.

241
00:25:19,124 --> 00:25:21,387
- Take that...
- Okay.

242
00:26:03,603 --> 00:26:06,780
Carioca.
That's what we call it.

243
00:26:06,824 --> 00:26:10,001
- Hm.
- Small enough for a farmer
to use anywhere,

244
00:26:10,044 --> 00:26:12,830
and strong enough
for any company to want.

245
00:26:12,873 --> 00:26:16,268
With this kind of power,
it will take a lot of gasoline.

246
00:26:16,311 --> 00:26:20,707
We start with the Morris
four-cylinder 1548 cc.

247
00:26:20,751 --> 00:26:24,058
Yeah, of course.
What we talked about.

248
00:26:24,102 --> 00:26:26,626
Here's what
we didn't talk about.

249
00:26:26,670 --> 00:26:29,324
- Two fuel tanks?
- Yes.

250
00:26:29,368 --> 00:26:30,717
Oh, fuck.

251
00:26:31,979 --> 00:26:32,937
Listen...

252
00:26:35,069 --> 00:26:36,767
- we start on gasoline.
- Mm-hm.

253
00:26:36,810 --> 00:26:39,726
But when the exhaust manifold
warms enough,

254
00:26:39,770 --> 00:26:44,688
we can cut off the gasoline
and release petroleum
from this tank.

255
00:26:44,731 --> 00:26:51,390
Maybe. The coil
would have to be hot enough
to vaporize the petroleum

256
00:26:51,433 --> 00:26:53,784
before it gets into
the carburetor.

257
00:26:53,827 --> 00:26:56,177
That's why
it'll be a copper coil.

258
00:26:58,049 --> 00:27:01,966
So, two types of fuel.
One cheap, one expensive.

259
00:27:02,009 --> 00:27:03,619
And a copper coil.

