346
00:36:25,485 --> 00:36:27,357
- Okay.
- The baby's coming.

347
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:28,662
- He's coming.
- Again.

348
00:36:28,706 --> 00:36:30,708
It's coming.
It's coming. Breathe.

349
00:36:30,751 --> 00:36:32,318
- Push, Clelia.

350
00:36:32,362 --> 00:36:35,278
Good. Breathe and push.

351
00:36:37,976 --> 00:36:39,586
- Push.

352
00:36:41,893 --> 00:36:43,982
She's getting the paper!
She's bleeding!

353
00:36:44,025 --> 00:36:45,288
Forceps!

354
00:36:45,331 --> 00:36:51,294
Ferruccio! Ferruccio!

355
00:37:05,656 --> 00:37:07,135
Can I help you?

356
00:37:07,788 --> 00:37:09,181
My wife is here!

357
00:37:31,159 --> 00:37:33,205
How is Clelia?

358
00:37:33,248 --> 00:37:36,164
The baby is fine.
It's a beautiful boy.

359
00:37:36,208 --> 00:37:37,644
Where is my wife?

360
00:37:39,167 --> 00:37:40,517
There was a problem.

361
00:37:51,571 --> 00:37:53,530
We weren't able
to stop the bleeding.

362
00:39:44,118 --> 00:39:47,687
We need to set a date
for the baby, for the baptism.

363
00:39:47,731 --> 00:39:49,341
Yes.

364
00:39:49,384 --> 00:39:51,386
You need to think about
other things now.

365
00:39:53,476 --> 00:39:54,520
Of course.

366
00:39:56,435 --> 00:39:59,612
May the seeds of the fruit
be planted with goodwill.

367
00:39:59,656 --> 00:40:01,962
And the harvest will be rich.

368
00:40:12,364 --> 00:40:13,800
- Ferruccio.
- Vito.

369
00:40:16,455 --> 00:40:17,543
So sorry about your wife.

370
00:40:17,587 --> 00:40:19,937
