things than grades.

485
00:49:47,460 --> 00:49:48,592
Like my mother?

486
00:49:50,985 --> 00:49:52,422
Like her.

487
00:49:52,465 --> 00:49:54,641
You still miss her, don't you?

488
00:49:56,165 --> 00:49:57,296
Yes.

489
00:49:58,645 --> 00:50:00,908
Why?

490
00:50:00,952 --> 00:50:03,259
Because she was beautiful,
like you.

491
00:50:03,302 --> 00:50:05,826
Is that why you
miss her so much?

492
00:50:15,793 --> 00:50:18,056
I miss her so much
because she was the kindest

493
00:50:18,100 --> 00:50:21,190
and the smartest person
I ever met.

494
00:50:22,713 --> 00:50:24,106
She understood
better than anyone

495
00:50:24,149 --> 00:50:27,152
the difference between
right and wrong.

496
00:50:27,196 --> 00:50:29,328
And for a lot of people
that's not so easy.

497
00:50:30,764 --> 00:50:32,244
She always did the right thing.

498
00:50:33,506 --> 00:50:35,204
She made it look easy.

499
00:50:38,163 --> 00:50:40,557
Annita's pretty great, too.

500
00:50:43,168 --> 00:50:44,256
She is.

501
00:50:49,218 --> 00:50:51,524
If your grades don't improve,
I'll buy you a Ferrari.

502
00:51:09,325 --> 00:51:10,761
Good day, mate.

503
00:51:10,804 --> 00:51:12,284
I'm looking for a job.

504
00:51:12,328 --> 00:51:14,112
Any inkling
on who I might see?

505
00:51:14,156 --> 00:51:18,334
Everyone's gone home.
Come back tomorrow.

506
00:51:18,377 --> 00:51:20,988
That's a pretty flash motor
you're working on there!

507
00:51:21,032 --> 00:51:23,643
- Australian?
- Nah, Kiwi.

508
00:51:23,687 --> 00:51:27,169
- What do you do?
- Anything needed for a car.

509
00:51:27,212 --> 00:51:31,085
I came here to turn a wrench.
I love the Italian motors, mate.

510
00:51:31,129 --> 00:51:33,262
Yeah, called in on Maserati,
Fiat, Ferrari,

511
00:51:33,305 --> 00:51:35,133
they all told me to piss off.

512
00:51:35,177 --> 00:51:36,395
What are we working on?

513
00:51:37,701 --> 00:51:38,876
Bad clutch.

514
00:51:48,712 --> 00:51:51,932
Whoever's been driving that car
needs a lesson or three.

515
00:51:51,976 --> 00:51:54,935
It's not the driver.
It's the clutch.

516
00:51:54,979 --> 00:51:56,981
Would that be
a matter of opinion?

517
00:51:59,766 --> 00:52:01,507
I want to modify
the tractor clutch,

518
00:52:01,551 --> 00:52:03,466
to use in the Ferrari.

519
00:52:03,509 --> 00:52:07,470
In your opinion,
what do I have to do?

520
00:52:07,513 --> 00:52:10,299
The disc and the plates
are pretty much the same.

521
00:52:11,604 --> 00:52:14,259
More than enough space
to mount it.

522
00:52:14,303 --> 00:52:16,000
I'd say you don't have to do
a bloody thing,

523
00:52:16,043 --> 00:52:17,393
you just put
the new clutch in.

524
00:52:17,436 --> 00:52:20,874
- I agree.
- I'll give a hand.

525
00:52:21,701 --> 00:52:22,963
What's your name?

526
00:52:23,007 --> 00:52:25,705
Wallace.
Bob Wallace. Yours?

527
00:52:25,749 --> 00:52:28,578
Ferruccio Lamborghini.

